Anyways, how to seed? You just leave your bittorrentclient on and you can see, after it has come to 100 %, it is still uploading. Then you are seeding.

But don't seed many files at once if you haven't got a hell of a broad broadband. Seed only about 1-2 torrents at one time. If one of them stop, which means 1) nobody is downloading 2) they are downloading from others. If thats the case, stop the torrent and start an other one. That way you are using your bandwidth ultimately.

And seed AT LEAST 1-2 ratio. I would suggest, if you have your computer on at night, around 5-10. That's what I do, and it's lovely to see like "uploaded: 24 GB - downloaded: 699 MB", isn't it?
